    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a pretty strong way to put it. Do you think there's any actual merit to the idea that substantive due process is essentially just judges making up laws based on their own personal values? Like, isn't that a bit of a stretch for a legal principle?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
